description: The File types name authority list (NAL) or Common Authority Table (CAT) is a controlled vocabulary listing file types used in the context of the with their authority code and label(s) in the 24 official languages of the EU (when available). The File types NAL is part of the Core Metadata (CM) used in the data exchange between the institutions involved in the legal decision making process and the Publications Office of the EU. The NAL is under governance of the Interinstitutional Metadata Maintenance Committee (IMMC) and maintained  by the Publications Office of the EU in its Metadata Registry (MDR)
